    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="436"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 322.112G64/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Ecuador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translations.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Ecuador</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: The last mail from Ecuador brought me
                    instructions from my Government to confer with your excellency over a petition
                    filed by Goo Kwai, a Chinaman naturalized in the United States, who wishes to
                    repair to Ecuador on a visit to his family.</p>
                <p>For that purpose and with your excellency’s kind note No. 11 of the 7th instant
                    before me, I have the honor to assure you that I shall be glad to talk over the
                    matter with you when I next call at the Department, of which I will let your
                    excellency know the evening before.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. S. Córdova</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
